# Barka project context

Before non-trivial changes (more than a one-line fix), read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) and [`CLAUDE.md`](../../CLAUDE.md) and follow them—including architecture notes, build/test commands (e.g. LocalStack for tests, `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` before push), and the working-style section in `CLAUDE.md` (e.g. check [`tasks/lessons.md`](../../tasks/lessons.md) when relevant).

If a task touches leadership, epochs, or flushes, apply the concurrency lesson in `tasks/lessons.md`.

When the user asks to commit, push, open a PR, or watch/fix CI until green, read and follow [`.cursor/skills/commit-push-pr-ci/SKILL.md`](../../.cursor/skills/commit-push-pr-ci/SKILL.md).
